()Workflow ka matlab hai – ek predefined sequence of tasks jo automatic ya semi-automatic chalti hai 
jab koi event trigger hota hai. 😎
workflow decide karta hai ki kaunsa kaam kab aur kaise hoga. Enterprise me ye Automation ka backbone hai.
🔷 1️⃣ Workflow kya hai?
Ye definition / design hai
XML/config hota hai
Static hota hai

👉 Example:-
OnboardingWorkflow.xml

👉 Isme:-
steps
transitions
rules

🔹 1️⃣ Workflow kya hai?
👉 Workflow = configuration + execution logic ka combination
💡 Simple:-
Design (XML/config)
Steps + flow control
Thoda Java/BeanShell logic

🔹 Kya Workflow data store karta hai?
👉 ❌ Workflow khud data store nahi karta
👉 ✅ Workflow sirf configuration/definition hota hai

🔹 1️⃣ Fir data kaha store hota hai?
👉 Data store hota hai:-

WorkflowCase ✅
WorkItem ✅
IdentityRequest ✅
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()🔹 1️⃣ WorkflowCase kya hai?
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()🔹 1️⃣ WorkflowCase kya hai?
👉 WorkflowCase = ek running workflow ka instance
💡 Simple samajh:-
Workflow = template / design
WorkflowCase = uska real running instance (runtime data)

()workflowcase:-
 SailPoint me WorkflowCase basically ek object hai jo workflow ke execution instance ko represent karta hai.
 Matlab jab bhi koi workflow trigger hota hai, ek WorkflowCase create hota hai, aur iske andar workflow ke sare state, 
 tasks, aur data track hote hain.WorkflowCase me work items, approvals, escalations store hote hain.

❗ Short Answer (direct):-
👉 WorkflowContext data leta hai → WorkflowCase se ✅
👉 Workflow se nahi ❌ kyuki workflow ke basis par workflowcase banata hai sailpoint.

🧠 Ab detail me samajh
🔷 1️⃣ Workflow kya hai?
Ye definition / design hai
XML/config hota hai
Static hota hai

👉 Example:-
OnboardingWorkflow.xml

👉 Isme:-
steps
transitions
rules
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔷 2️⃣ WorkflowCase kya hai?
Ye runtime instance hai
Jab workflow run hota hai tab banta hai
Isme actual data store hota hai
👉 Example:-
john.doe ka onboarding run → ek WorkflowCase banega
👉 Isme hota hai:-
arguments
status
messages
variables
----------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ WorkflowCase me kya kya store hota hai?
✔️ 1. Basic Info
id → unique ID
workflowName → kaunsa workflow chal raha hai
status → Running / Completed / Failed

✔️ 2. Variables (bahut important 🔥)
👉 Workflow me jo bhi data pass hota hai:
identityName
requestId
approvalId
custom variables
identityName = user1
requestId = REQ-101

✔️ 3. Current Step Info
Abhi workflow ka kaunsa step chal raha hai
Next step kya hai

✔️ 4. Work Items (Approval tasks)
👉 Agar approval step hai:-
Manager approval
Admin approval
➡️ Ye sab WorkItem ke form me store hota hai

✔️ 5. Approval Data
Approvers list
Approval status
Comments

✔️ 6. History / Audit
Kis step pe kya hua
Kisne approve/reject kiya
Kab hua

✔️ 7. Timestamps
Created date
Modified date
Completion time
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 4️⃣ Ye data workflowcase me DB me store hota hai ya temporary?
👉 ✅ YES — DB me store hota hai (important 🔥)

✔️ Temporary bhi hota hai?
👉 ❌ Sirf memory me nahi hota
👉 ✅ Main data DB me persist hota hai
💡 But:-
Runtime me memory + DB dono use hota hai.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
✔️ 3. workflowcase me data Kyun DB me store hota hai? (Very Important 🔥)
🔸 1. System restart ke liye
Server restart ho gaya → workflow wapas resume ho sakta hai
🔸 2. Long running workflows
Approval 2 din pending hai → data safe rahe
🔸 3. Audit / tracking
Kisne approve kiya, kab kiya → sab store hota hai
🔸 4. Resume / retry
Workflow fail ho gaya → dubara start ya continue kar sakte hain
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔷 3️⃣ WorkflowContext kya hai?
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔷 3️⃣ WorkflowContext kya hai?
Ye execution helper / wrapper hai
WorkflowCase ko access karne ka tool

🔥 Relationship (sabse important):-
Workflow (design)
      ↓
WorkflowCase (runtime data)
      ↓
WorkflowContext (access / execution)

❗ Short Answer (direct):-
👉 WorkflowContext data leta hai → WorkflowCase se ✅
👉 Workflow se nahi ❌ kyuki workflow ke basis par workflowcase banata hai sailpoint.

()WorkflowContext kya hai?
WorkflowContext ek object/class hai jo current workflow execution ke environment aur data ko represent karta hai SailPoint me.
Matlab: Jab bhi workflow run hoti hai, WorkflowContext me saari information available hoti hai jaise:-
Workflow ke variables
Arguments (inputs)
Execution status
Output/result
Ye basically workflow ke “runtime environment” ka container hai.
ye value store nahi karta.aur conversion me workflowcontext ke andar ke workflowcase/workflow use hota hai.
🔹 1️⃣ “WorkflowContext value store nahi karta”
👉 ✔️ Bilkul sahi (mostly)
WorkflowContext ek runtime object hai
Ye temporary hota hai
Execution ke time hi exist karta hai
👉 Isme:-
values hold hoti hain (temporary)
but database me store nahi hoti
👉 Example:-
context.getArguments();  // temporary data

🔹 2️⃣ “conversion me workflowcontext ke andar ke workflowcase/workflow use hota hai”
👉 ✔️ Ye bhi sahi hai — aur ye important concept hai
Jab tu likhta hai:-
context.toXml();

👉 Actually hota kya hai:-
WorkflowContext → internally → WorkflowCase / SailPointObject → toXml() me convert karta hai.

--------------------------------------
🔹 WorkflowContext ke main uses:-
Arguments set aur get karna
Workflow ke input ya output variables ko handle karna
Execution status check karna
Workflow successful hai ya failed
Workflow ke results access karna
Workflow me messages add karna
Launch message, UI message, logs

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 4️⃣ WorkflowService kya hai?
👉 WorkflowService = class jo workflows ko start / manage / execute karti hai
👉 Package:-
sailpoint.api.WorkflowService
💡 Simple line me:-
👉 “Workflow chalane ka engine” = WorkflowService

🔹 3️⃣ Ye kya karta hai?
WorkflowService ka kaam:-
✔️ 1. Workflow start karna
New workflow instance create karta hai
✔️ 2. Variables pass karna
Workflow me data bhejta hai
✔️ 3. Workflow execute karna
Steps run karta hai
✔️ 4. Workflow monitor karna
Status check karta hai